               <p>WILLIAM MARSHALL. I live in <placeName id="t18310106-44-crimeloc258">Brick-lane, Spitalfields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310106-44-crimeloc258" type="placeName" value="Brick-lane, Spitalfields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310106-44-crimeloc258" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310106-44-off256 t18310106-44-crimeloc258"></join>, and am a <rs id="t18310106-44-viclabel259" type="occupation">brush-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310106-44-victim459 t18310106-44-viclabel259"></join> - the prisoner was in my employ, and worked on my premises. I suspected him, and desired the officer to watch, and on the 18th of December, about six o'clock, as he was leaving work, he brought him into my shop, and four bundles of bristles were found on him; he had no right to take any thing off my premises -I had missed property several times.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310106-44-person460">
                  WILLIAM 
                  WHEATLEY
               <interp inst="t18310106-44-person460" type="surname" value="WHEATLEY"></interp>
